  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Blogging with Octopress -- Posts, Comments and SEO]]></title>
    <link href="http://voice.lawrencesun.info/posts/2013/12/21/blogging-with-octopress/"/>
    <updated>2013-12-21T17:34:23+00:00</updated>
    <id>http://voice.lawrencesun.info/posts/2013/12/21/blogging-with-octopress</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Run the following code to generate a new post:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="n">rake</span> <span class="n">new_post</span><span class="o">[</span><span class="s2">&quot;new post&quot;</span><span class="o">]</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Octopress uses <a href="http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/">Markdown</a>, which&rsquo;s clean and simple as writing a text. I am still learning how to use it well.</p>

<p>In order to get better SEO optimizations, add <em>keywords</em> and <em>description</em> at the beginning of each post after <em>catagories</em>.</p>

<p>Octopress also allows us to add google analytics. Simply add Analytics ID in _config.yml file and add included</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="p">{</span><span class="o">%</span> <span class="kp">include</span> <span class="n">google_analytics</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">html</span> <span class="o">%</span><span class="p">}</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>in _includes/custom/after_footer.html.</p>

<p>If you want to add comments after each post like me, add Disqus shortname in _config.yml file and set URL, username etc. in Disqus Setting.</p>
]]></content>
